+### D.2.1 Runtime / dependency contract (pinned — not "lightweight, TBD")
+
+The first draft hand-waved "lightweight job, maybe no `uv sync`" while also
+promising `check-jsonschema` validation, which has a real dependency. Pinned
+resolution — the lite job needs **exactly** what `docs-lint` + `schema-validity`
+already use, and **no `uv sync`**:
+
+- **`python3`** (via `actions/setup-python@v5`, matching the `schema-validity`
+  job) — runs `check-docs-commands.py` itself and `eden-manual <sub> --help`
+  (`eden-manual` is a system-`python3` script with no workspace imports, so bare
+  `python3` suffices; **no `uv sync`/workspace install**).
+- **`pipx`** to run the pinned `check-jsonschema==0.29.4` for embedded-fixture
+  validation — the *identical* tool+version `schema-validity` invokes
+  ([`ci.yml`](../../.github/workflows/ci.yml) `schema-validity` step). The
+  extractor shells out to it rather than importing `jsonschema`, so the lite job
+  inherits zero Python dependencies of its own.
+- **`bash`** (preinstalled) for `bash -n` and `setup-experiment.sh --help`.
+
+So the job is genuinely light (setup-python + pipx, no `uv sync`, no Docker) but
+its dependency list is now explicit and the headline command
+`python3 scripts/check-docs-commands.py --strict` is runnable as written both
+locally (where `pipx`/`python3` are on PATH) and in CI. If review prefers the
+extractor to `import jsonschema` directly instead of shelling to `pipx`, that
+trades the pin-parity-with-`schema-validity` property for a `uv`-managed dep —
+call it out; the shell-to-pinned-pipx path is chosen to keep the two
+schema-validating jobs byte-identical in what they enforce.
+
